SIMPLE: sclerotic
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sclerotic
<hw>Scle*rot"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>sklhro`s</grk> hard: cf. F. <ets>scl⟦eacute⟧rotique</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Hard; firm; indurated; -- applied especially in anatomy
to the firm outer coat of the eyeball, which is often cartilaginous and
sometimes bony.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the sclerotic
coat of the eye; sclerotical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Affected with sclerosis;
sclerosed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sclerotic parenchyma</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>,
<cd>sclerenchyma. By some writers a distinction is made, <xex>sclerotic
parenchyma</xex> being applied to tissue composed of cells with the
walls hardened but not thickened, and <xex>sclerenchyma</xex> to tissue
composed of cells with the walls both hardened and
thickened.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sclerotic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sclerotic
<hw>Scle*rot"ic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>scl⟦eacute⟧rotique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The
sclerotic coat of the eye.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sclerotic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sclerotic
<hw>Scle*rot"ic</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining
to, or designating, an acid obtained from ergot or the sclerotium of a
fungus growing on rye.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sclerotical</ent>⟦br⟧
